#text=I 'm so excited for my trip to Florida !
#text=It 's going to be warm and I 'm looking forward to visiting Disney World .
#text=The most exciting part will be the plane ride .
#text=When I arrive at the airport , I get into the check in line .
#text=I show the woman at the counter my ticket .
#text=She asks to see either my driver 's license or a passport .
#text=She asks me how many suitcases I will be brining with me .
#text=She prints off stickers to put on my bags so that they know which plane to put my bags on .
#text=Next , she prints out my boarding pass .
#text=I will need this to be able to get onto the plane .
#text=She tells me that my plane will be leaving from Gate A7 .
#text=I follow the signs that point towards Gate A7 .
#text=Before I can enter the '' `` A '' '' terminal , I must go through a security check point .
#text=I take a plastic bin and place all my loose belongings in there - like my backpack , keys and cell phone .
#text=I also must remove my shoes and place them in a bin .
#text=The bins run along a conveyor belt and into an x-ray machine .
#text=People monitor the x-ray machine to make sure there is nothing dangerous in my belongings .
#text=A man waves at me to walk through a metal detector .
#text=It 's just like walking through an open door .
#text=After I am cleared at security , I collect my bags and head to the gate .
#text=Thirty minutes later , my plane has arrived and an airline employee announces that we will be boarding .
#text=The plane boards according to what row you are seated in .
#text=Luckily , I 'm in row one so I get to go on the plane first !
#text=After everyone is seated and their carry on bags are either placed in the upper storage bins or under out seats , the flight attendant announces we are ready to take off !
#text=I buckle my seatbelt and then the plane slowly taxis to the runway .
#text=The friendly flight attendant talks about safety procedures while we are driving to the runway .
#text=Within two minutes , the plane starts moving faster and faster and before I know it , we are up in the air !
#text=Two of the flight attendants come over and offer me a drink and a snack .
#text=I choose a Diet Coke and some pretzels .
#text=While flying , I totally forget I 'm up in the air .
#text=It 's a bit noisy , as if riding in a train , but I forget we are n't on the ground ... until I look outside and see the clouds passing by .
#text=The pilot comes on the PA system a few times to announce things like cruising altitude and the current weather temperature in Florida .
#text=About two and half hours after take off , the pilot asks us to prepare for landing .
#text=We have to put our seats upright and make sure we are buckled in .
#text=I can feel the plane slowly descending .
#text=My ears feel a bit uncomfortable from the change in air pressure .
#text=I can see houses and trees getting closer .
#text=The plane bumps once when the landing gear touches the ground .
#text=We roll smoothly to the end of the runway and then taxi over to the gate .
#text=I gather up my belongings and thank the flight crew for a wonderful flight .
#text=I ca n't wait to start my vacation !
